      "id": 1,
      "text": "Alexander Turney Stewart founded Garden City in 1869, designing wide avenues, tree‑lined streets, and a private railroad to make it a planned village.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15,
        16
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.gardencityny.net/228/Village-History"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "After Stewart’s death, his wife Cornelia built the Cathedral of the Incarnation, a landmark Episcopal church that still stands in Garden City.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4,
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.gardencityny.net/228/Village-History"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Stewart’s heirs founded the Garden City Company, which guided the community’s growth until the village incorporated in 1919.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.britannica.com/place/Garden-City-New-York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Charles Lindbergh stayed at the Garden City Hotel while preparing for his 1927 transatlantic flight, a scene later filmed in the movie 'The Spirit of St. Louis'.",
